    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bamboo clappers of Hawaii made by cutting most of a length of bamboo into narrow longitudinal strips, stopping short of one end with a natural node which serves as a handle. They are struck against the palm of the free hand or other part of the body like a switch, struck in pairs against each other, or shaken like rattles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleppers van bamboe in smalle langwerpige stroken gesneden, waarbij een knoop dienst doet als handvat; bespeeld door ze tegen de palm van de vrije hand te slaan of tegen een ander deel van het lichaam, ook in paren tegen elkaar geslagen of geschud als rammelaars; Hawaï.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指夏威夷的竹製響板。將一大段竹子切成許多縱向細條，具有天然莖節的一端不切開，用來當作握柄；像鞭子一般敲擊空手的手掌或身體其他部位，兩兩成雙互相敲擊，或是像搖晃樂器一樣搖動。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bambusklapper aus Hawaii, bestehend aus der Länge nach in dünne Streifen geschnittenen Bambusröhren, die kurz vor einem natürlichen Knoten enden, der als Grff dient. Die Klappern werden gegen den Handteller der freien Hand oder einen anderen Köperteil geschlagen wie eine Gerte, paarweise gegeneinander geschlagen oder wie Rasseln geschüttelt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
